==English==

===Etymology===
Refers to the [[w:Fourth of July|Fourth of July]], which is [[w:Independence Day|Independence Day]] in the [[w:United States of America|United States]]. The specific phrase likely originates with the song "Yankee Doodle Dandy" which opens with "''I'm a Yankee Doodle Dandy / A Yankee Doodle, do or die / A real live nephew of my [[Uncle Sam|uncle Sam]]'s / Born on the Fourth of July''".

